  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/noria/ontology/alarmMonitoredAttribute">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty"/>
    <rdfs:label>alarmMonitoredAttribute</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">The Monitored attributes parameter, when present, defines one or more attributes of the managed object and their corresponding values at the time of the alarm.
Managed object definers may specify the set of attributes which are of interest, if any.
This allows, for example, the timely reporting of changing conditions prevalent at the time of the alarm.
</rdfs:comment>
